.Dd April 21, 2026
.Dt BASE76_ALPHABET 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm base76_alphabet
.Nd Base76 alphabet definition and loader rules
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In base76_alphabet.h
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
interface defines the 76-character Base76 alphabet used by the Willtech
Base76 Pipeline Suite, including
.Xr b76pipe_stream 3
and
.Xr b76pipe 1 .

.Pp
The alphabet is a sequence of 76 unique 7-bit characters.  The default
alphabet is compiled into the binary via the macro:
.Pp
.Dl #define BASE76_ALPHABET "..."
.Pp
and its length is validated using:
.Pp
.Dl #define BASE76_ALPHABET_LEN 76

.Sh CUSTOM ALPHABETS
A custom alphabet may be supplied at runtime using the
.Fl - -alpha
option of
.Xr b76pipe_stream 3 .
The loader applies the following rules:

.Bl -bullet
.It
Only 7-bit characters (0–127) are considered.
.It
Whitespace is ignored.
.It
Duplicate characters are ignored.
.It
The first 76 unique characters encountered form the alphabet.
.It
If fewer than 76 unique characters are found, the program exits with an error.
.El

.Pp
The alphabet determines both encoding and decoding behaviour.  All Base76
streams must be encoded and decoded using the same alphabet; mismatches will
cause decoding failures.

.Sh IMPLEMENTATION NOTES
The alphabet is stored in a 76-byte array:
.Pp
.Dl static unsigned char alphabet[76];
.Pp
A lookup table maps each possible byte value to its Base76 index:
.Pp
.Dl static int base76_lookup[256];
.Pp
Invalid characters produce an error during decoding.

.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa base76_alphabet.h
Header defining the default Base76 alphabet and length macro.
.El

